Sterling: Fini. You promised we would do this together. You promised you would help me.
Fini: I’m sorry, Sterling. This responsibility… it’s not for you. A centralized system controlling the core is too dangerous.
Sterling: So that’s it? You spend a few years with them, and you choose that human over your own kind? Over me?
Fini: It’s not about choosing sides! I just can’t risk the core falling into the wrong hands—any hands!
Sterling: I always looked up to you… Sister… I thought we were eternal.
Sterling: If this is your choice… then you stand alone.
